                    <li>‚õ™ Spiritual/religious community centers</li>
                    <li>ü§ù Mutual aid during hardships</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h3>Economic Challenges</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>üí∏ No access to capital or credit</li>
                    <li>üöÇ Limited transport to markets</li>
                    <li>üìà Vulnerable to global market forces</li>
                    <li>üè≠ Industrial Revolution bypassed most of Asia</li>
                    <li>üíº 83% of Chinese workforce in agriculture (1952)</li>
                    <li>‚öñÔ∏è Heavy taxation and government levies</li>
                    <li>üåç International competition affecting local products</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Adaptation Timeline -->
        <div class="timeline">
            <h2>Could You Adapt to This Lifestyle?</h2>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <h3>Physical Challenges</h3>
                <p>The transition from modern convenience to dawn-to-dusk manual labor would be brutal. Using basic tools for farming, carrying water by hand, and the constant physical demands would challenge anyone accustomed to modern life.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <h3>Food Security Stress</h3>
                <p>The anxiety of one bad harvest potentially meaning starvation creates a stress level modern life rarely imposes. The uncertainty and lack of control over survival would be mentally exhausting.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <h3>Social Limitations</h3>
                <p>Limited personal freedoms, especially for women, rigid social hierarchies, and lack of individual choice in life paths would feel suffocating by today's standards.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <h3>Potential Benefits</h3>
                <p>However, the deep connection to natural cycles, strong community bonds, multi-generational wisdom, and life's simplicity offer social support systems we've largely lost in modern society.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Footer -->
        <div class="footer">
            <h3>About This Project</h3>
            <p>This interactive page explores ordinary life in rural Asia during the Industrial Revolution (18th-19th centuries).</p>
            <p>Research conducted using web sources and academic materials to understand daily life, social structures, and economic challenges.</p>
            <p>Created as an educational resource to visualize historical living conditions and promote understanding of pre-industrial life.</p>
